post_text:
Lorraine Mullen will be completing 31 years of service today at Maywood Public School. She has worked as the head cook for 18 years, prior to that she was the assistant cook and had janitorial responsibilities. Preparing the meals, serving students, creating recipes, and unloading trucks were some of the tasks Lorraine performed daily. Caring for the students was something she always did and the students always thanked her daily for the meals she prepared. Lorraine, we wish you nothing but the best as you enter retirement, thank you for 31 tremendous years of service to Maywood Public Schools.

Sincerely,

Students & Staff of MPS
text:
Lorraine Mullen will be completing 31 years of service today at Maywood Public School. She has worked as the head cook for 18 years, prior to that she was the assistant cook and had janitorial responsibilities. Preparing the meals, serving students, creating recipes, and unloading trucks were some of the tasks Lorraine performed daily. Caring for the students was something she always did and the students always thanked her daily for the meals she prepared. Lorraine, we wish you nothing but the best as you enter retirement, thank you for 31 tremendous years of service to Maywood Public Schools.

Sincerely,

Students & Staff of MPS

Maywood School Families,
Due to COVID-19 pandemic and the force of school closure, Maywood Public Schools will be offering lunch and breakfast for students. If you would like breakfast and lunch delivered to your residence, you will need to contact the school one day prior in advance by 1:00 PM. There will not be choices, the cooks will prepare the meal and it will be delivered. When you call in or email to request a meal, you also will need to leave your address and a phone number to be contacted at, in case a question arises. Families can call the office at 308-362-4223 or email the school at maywood.transportation@maywoodtigers.org. Meals will be started to be served on 3/19/20. If you have questions, please call the office at 308-362-4223 or email the address that is above. Thanks

post_text: FFA CDE results. The nursery and landscape team earned a second place finish qualifying for state with Eli, Jenna, and Lexi earning blue ribbons and Jon earning a red ribbon. The farm business management team earned a red ribbon and will compete at state with Jason and McKenna earning blue ribbons and Olivia earning a white ribbon. The Ag Communications team earned a red 4th place finish and will submit their media plan to state for a wild card spot. The vet science team wrapped up our teams earning 4th place and a red ribbon. Natalie and McKenna earned blue ribbons; Chloe, Kiley, and Kohl earned red ribbons and Olivia earned a white ribbon. Great work Maywood FFA members!
